Description:
Building contract works to facilitate the installation of a new exhibit within the Newcastle Discovery Museum.  Works will include demolitions and alterations, forming new office space, finishes and alterations to M&E installations.

Tender Publication Date - 10 May 2017. 

The relevant tender documents are available for download from the NEPO Pro Contract Tendering Portal.

In order to access and view the published tender documents please visit the following tendering portal website address, search for the opportunity and then register your interest.

Tendering Portal - https://procontract.due-north.com

Upload of documentation can take some time, please ensure you provide adequate time to do this ahead of the submission deadline.

Please note quotations must be received no later than the date and time stated on the e-tendering system. Late submissions will not be accepted. 

The Tender is made up of the following documents: 
Invitation to Tender Part 1; 
Invitation to Tender Part 2; 
Schedule 1 - Specification; 
Appendix 1 - List of Tender Drawings; 
Appendix 2 - Architectural Drawings; 
Appendix 3 - Specification of Materials and Workmanship; 
Appendix 4 - Electrical Installation Drawings and Specification; Appendix 5 - CDM Pre-Construction Information; 
Appendix 5C - Asbestos Survey; 
Schedule 2 - Contract; 
Appendix 1A - Preliminaries Part 1; 
Appendix 1B - Preliminaries Part 2; 
Appendix 1C - Preliminaries Pricing Schedule; 
Appendix 2 - Bill No.2 - Alteration Works; 
Appendix 3 - Bill No.3 - Electrical Services Installations; 
Appendix 4 - Bill No.4 - Provisional Sums; 
Appendix 5 - General Summary; 
Appendix 6 - Hot Works Appendices; 
Appendix 7 - Request for Inspection of the Works Appendix; Appendix 8 - Contract Schedule A - CDM Contract Amendment; Appendix 9 - Contract Schedule B - Public Sector Supplement; Schedule 3 - Form of Tender; 
Schedule 4 - Certificate of Non-Collusion and Non-Canvassing; Schedule 5 - Pre-Qualification Questionnaire; 
and Schedule 6 - Tender Response Form.
